Package se.jbee.inject.bind

Interface Summary
BasicBinder The minimal BasicBinder.TypedBasicBinder to bind should illustrate the stages.
BasicBinder.RootBasicBinder The ROOT- BasicBinder.RootBasicBinder.
BasicBinder.ScopedBasicBinder A Scope had been defined.
BasicBinder.TargetedBasicBinder Bindings have been restricted and are just effective within a special scope defined before using BasicBinder.ScopedBasicBinder.injectingInto(Instance)-clauses.
BasicBinder.TypedBasicBinder<T> The Type of the Resource defined is already given using BasicBinder.bind(Instance)
Bindings The binding-builders are just utilities to construct calls to Bindings.add(Resource, Supplier, Scope, Source)
Bootstrapper The basic idea is to split the binding process into 2 steps: installing modules and do bindings in the installed modules.
Bootstrapper.ModularBootstrapper<M>  
Bundle A bundle installs sub-bundles and Modules.
Bundler Determines all reachable Bundles starting from a root Bundle.
Const  
ConstructionStrategy A ConstructionStrategy picks the Constructor to use to construct objects of a given Class.
Edition An Edition decides wich features are contained in a specific setup.
Extension<E extends Enum<E> & Extension<E,? super T>,T>  
Feature<T extends Enum<T>> Features can be used to model more fine grained Edition by using enums as the options to chose from.
Linker<T>  
ModularBundle<M> A Bundle that does different installation for different options.
Modulariser Determines / extracts the Module result from a root Bundle.
Module Bindings are defined with Modules while Bundle are used to group multiple Modules and Bundles what allows to build graphs of Bundles with Modules as leafs.
 

Class Summary
Binder The default implementation of the BasicBinder that provides a lot of utility methods to improve readability and keep binding compact.
Binder.RootBinder  
Binder.ScopedBinder  
Binder.TargetedBinder  
Binder.TypedBinder<T>  
Binder.TypedElementBinder<E> This kind of bindings actually re-map the []-type so that the automatic behavior of returning all known instances of the element type will no longer be used whenever the bind made applies.
BinderModule The default utility Module almost always used.
Bootstrap Utility to create an Injector context from Bundles and Modules.
BootstrapperBundle The default utility Bundle that is a Bootstrap as well so that bindings can be declared nicer.
BootstrappingModule  
Constants Constants are used to model configurations of the Bootstrapping process through one enum for each configurable property.
Extend  
Link  
ModularBootstrapperBundle<M> The default ustility base class for ModularBundles.
 

Enum Summary
BuildinBundle Installs all the build-in functionality by using the core API.
